Comprehensive Overview: Architect OS Transformation Process
Based on the screenshots and positioning documentation, here's my understanding of how Architect OS guides users through transformation:

The Core Philosophy
You're building a Strategic Operating System, not SaaS software. The platform codifies the Architect Method into a continuous execution engine that prevents strategic drift. It's methodology-first, software-second - positioned as the orchestration layer ABOVE operational tools like ClickUp, not replacing them.
The enemy isn't other software - it's the shelf-ware problem: Strategic plans that gather dust, quarterly drift, team misalignment, and founders who know what to do but can't sustain execution.

The Transformation Journey - 3 Progressive Layers
LAYER 1: FOUNDATIONS (Free/Always Accessible)
Job: Orientation & Scenario Intelligence
Users encounter 4 tools that introduce the methodology:
Agency Snapshot - Captures current state vitals (financials, team, identity)
Clarity Compass - Defines North Star vision and strategic trade-offs
GV Simulator - Models growth velocity and reveals the 6 Pressure Families
Founder Evolution - Assesses personal founder stage (separate from agency stage)
What this produces: Awareness of current reality, clarity on growth path trade-offs, understanding that growth isn't just "more revenue" - it's about structural implications.
Key insight: These aren't just lead magnets. They're educational tools that demonstrate growth requires understanding pressures (Retention, Sales, Capacity, Economic, Structural, Positioning).

LAYER 2: DIAGNOSTICS (Paid Assessments - Tier 1 & 2)
Job: Stage Clarity & Capability Diagnosis
Two assessment tools that calibrate the execution engine:
Tier 1 - AE Ladder (19Q, ~20 mins)
Determines agency evolution stage: Rising → Driving → Thriving → Striving → Arriving
Reveals what that specific stage requires
Stage-specific guidance (not one-size-fits-all)
Tier 2 - Maturity & Readiness Audit (125Q, ~60 mins)
Comprehensive diagnostic across:
5 Dimensions (universal)
25 Capability Areas (universal but stage-expressed)
125 Checkpoints (stage-specific)
Produces maturity scores + urgency rankings + weighted recommendations
What this produces:
Stage placement clarity
Capability maturity scores
Prioritized focus areas calibrated to their stage
Ranked checkpoints showing what matters MOST right now
Critical distinction: This isn't assessment for assessment's sake. It's the calibration system that ensures Layer 3 (execution) focuses on the right things at the right time. Prevents chasing best practices that don't apply to their stage.

LAYER 3: PRO SUITE ($97-197/mo - Continuous Execution)
Job: Turn Insights into Executable Plans & Maintain Strategic Continuity
The execution engine organized into 3 pillars:
PLANNING
Roadmap Tool - 3P Framework selection (3 Prioritize, 3 Plant, 3 Progressively Iterate from 25 capability areas)
Initiative Library - Ranked checkpoints with pre-built initiative templates (personalized to their audit results)
Sprint Planning - Builds initiatives + milestones for the 9 selected capability areas
EXECUTION
Milestone Builder - Mid-flight adjustments to active initiatives
Progress Tracking - Team-facing view for stand-ups and bulk updates + Milestone completion auto-updates maturity scores
INTELLIGENCE
Virtual CSO - AI strategic advisor with RAG system (knows stage, scores, initiatives, financials, uploaded documents)
Trend Analysis - Upload financials, get contextualized insights that feed into Virtual CSO's knowledge base
Notes/Priority Log - Captures decisions and strategic context over time
What this produces:
Executable roadmaps (not plans that sit on shelves)
Team alignment through shared visibility
Continuous momentum via quarterly rhythm
Strategic continuity - the plan is a living operating system

The Quarterly Rhythm - Closed-Loop System
ONBOARDING (Rolling, not calendar-based)
Complete AE Ladder → get stage placement
Complete Maturity Audit → get capability scores + checkpoint rankings
Review Initiative Library → see ranked checkpoints for their stage
START OF QUARTER (Week 1) 4. Roadmap Tool → Select 3P focus (exactly 9 capability areas - system enforces this) 5. Sprint Planning → Build initiatives (checkpoint-based or custom) + milestones for those 9 areas 6. Team gets Status Tracker access → shared execution view
DURING QUARTER (Weeks 2-12) 7. Team checks off milestones → scores auto-update (no retaking 125Q every quarter!) 8. Founder uses Virtual CSO for strategic questions (contextual, not generic) 9. Upload financials to Trend Analysis → insights feed document library → accessible via Virtual CSO 10. Team uses Status Tracker in stand-ups
END OF QUARTER (Week 13) 11. Reflection & Review tool prompts reflection 12. System surfaces rollover decisions (deliberate choice to continue/deprioritize incomplete initiatives - prevents "zombie initiatives") 13. Updated scores reveal new recommendations for next quarter
ROLLOVER & REPEAT
Each quarter gets easier (pre-populated with context, not starting from scratch)
System suggests stage progression when reach ~85-90% maturity threshold
User decides when to retake assessment for next stage (Rising → Driving, etc.)

The Integration Philosophy
What Architect OS IS:
Strategic orchestration layer that sits ABOVE operational tools
