Makes existing expert investments (consultants, fractional execs) 10x more effective by ensuring their recommendations get implemented and sustained
What it's NOT:
Not replacing QuickBooks (you're not their accounting system)
Not replacing Power BI (you're not their BI dashboard)
Not replacing ClickUp/Monday (you're the strategic brain, they're the operational limbs)
Not a one-time deliverable - it's a continuous operating system
Future integrations enhance, not replace:
QuickBooks sync for automatic financial data
Task manager integrations to push milestones
Position as hub that connects everything to strategic roadmap

Critical User Experience Principles I'm Understanding:
Progressive Disclosure - Don't show all 125 checkpoints at once; default to "Top 10 for your stage"
Intelligent Defaults - System recommends 3P focus based on scores; founder can accept/modify
Golden Threads - Clear paths from assessment → planning → execution → progress (every score should link to initiatives)
Automated Quarterly Transitions - System proactively prompts review/rollover/planning (not manual founder memory)
Team vs Founder Views - Team sees Status Tracker only (execution focus); founder sees full strategic complexity
Continuous Intelligence - Every data upload (financials, documents) feeds Virtual CSO's contextual knowledge
Reduced Friction Over Time - Q2 should be EASIER than Q1 (rollover + defaults + accumulated context)

